table I worked in a 2nd kite of 3.. the two remaining statics on the north side, plus the single spawn on the north side of the big isle.<br><br>15 game hours later.. I'm an Evoker.  =) =)  out of 54 almost as quick as I went into it.  Hence the /bounce!<br><br>I do have a question though.  My wizard mentor said that 55 and 56 would &quot;fly&quot; by at these islands.. however I did a couple test kites.. same ones I was doing before.. and my bar moved less than it did in the 54 hell level thing (a quarter blue in 55 where I was getting a half blue in 54).<br><br>Do I need to be on the big island now at 55 to keep seeing decent movement on the exp bar? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarmok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Armok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/30/01 9:50:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /bounce - raptor question</span><hr size=1> You can stay at small isle all the way to 58.  The main problem with small isle is that it is more often camped. Being able to break large isle just gives you more options and is more likely to ensure you a kiting spot.<br><br>As for your levelling question:<br>51-53 are hell levels<br>54-58 are double hell levels<br>59 is a triple hell level<br><br>In addition to taking roughly double the experience of a normal level, each level from 54-58 takes a bit more than the one before.<br><br>- Armok Komra &lt;Triton&gt;<br>Sorcerer of Povar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uapokkberzerk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Apokk Berzerk</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/30/01 11:00:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://142.55.42.238/apokk_head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /bounce - raptor question</span><hr size=1> I wouldn't do it at 53, sure IF you have decent mana gear you could pull it off with a bit of med kiting and harvesting, but lets face it, you are going to be utterly OOM after each kite...that's a full med cycle each time...ughhhh<br><br>Go to CS come back at 55 and do the raptors to 58, i'm not quite finished yet myself. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><html><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=12421"><img src="http://apokkberzerk.homestead.com/files/apokk_sig/apokk.jpg"></img></A></html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utegellan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tegellan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/30/01 12:18:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /bounce - raptor question</span><hr size=1>  The only advantage large isle holds over small is that it has 2 VRs, when you are in your later levels pulling them yields better exp, but getting it down so you can do it with no adds is tough to say the least.<br><br> <p> <i>Tegellan Fey`Brandhe</i><BR> Evoker of the Fifth Order<Br> The Circle of Eternity - Veeshan<BR> <a href="mailto:tegellan@hotmail.com">tegellan@hotmail.com</a><BR><i>-I am the romancer. The burning passion that consumes the flesh</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujerrek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jerrek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/30/01 12:50:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /bounce - raptor question</span><hr size=1> I did two kites on the large isle while in 54, and I was either hallucinating, or those kites of 4 (3 reg 1 VR), gave me the same exp as the complete small isle+ (6 reg 1 VR) did.<br><br>I'll test it out some more later this week.<br><br>Oh.. and I did quad 3 regs + 1 VR at 53 and had 20m left over.  No med kiting, no harvesting.  I seem to have less mana left from using PoL than I did using PoF.. and either way I have to finish the VR off with a draught at the end.  Still trying to figure that one out.<br><br>I'm looking forward to the raptor guide that's being written.. see how the small isle strategy compares to the one that I developed after a while of being there. =)  And.. to see another interpretation of the big isle strategy.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uelupiousebonshire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elupious Ebonshire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/30/01 11:12:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/bwest92/Elupious.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /bounce - raptor question</span><hr size=1> I did 4 regular raptors at 52-53.  Then I did 1 VR and 3 regulars at 54-55.  At 56-58 I started doing 2 VRs and 2 regulars.  I tried doing all 3 VRs at 57, but the added time to pull made it not really worth it.  It didnt really matter which island I was on until I needed to get 2 VRs, although small isle was a little easier to pull from since there was only 1 wanderer.  At 59 I got sick of the raptors and did Othmirs till 60, they gave about the same exp and had much better loot, I would recommend them starting at 57 if you have Pillar of Flame. <p><BR><font color="#ff0000">Elupious Ebonshire<BR>Sorcerer of the 60th Circle<BR>Officer of Union<BR>Solusek Ro</font><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utegellan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tegellan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/31/01 4:55:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /bounce - raptor question</span><hr size=1>  In my time of kiting raptors the exp on the small and large isle are exactly the same, the levels on the raptors you get varies and hence the exp can be a little different, that is probably what happened to you Jerrek <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br> <p> <i>Tegellan Fey`Brandhe</i><BR> Evoker of the Fifth Order<Br> The Circle of Eternity - Veeshan<BR> <a href="mailto:tegellan@hotmail.com">tegellan@hotmail.com</a><BR><i>-I am the romancer. The burning passion that consumes the flesh</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarmok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Armok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/31/01 9:39:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /bounce - raptor question</span><hr size=1> Jerrek wrote:<br>&quot;I'm looking forward to the raptor guide that's being written.. &quot;<br><br>erm... which raptor guide is this?  I wrote one a while back that got moved to the library section. There's also a web page with raptor pulling info posted in a nice graphical format, but that one suggests pulling raptors to chessboard isle which is a bad idea in my experience. Is someone working on another raptor guide?<br><br>- Armok Komra &lt;Triton&gt;<br>Sorcerer of Povar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujerrek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jerrek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/31/01 10:07:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /bounce - raptor question</span><hr size=1> Goatherain De'Verconis - the gent that did the otter thingie that so many people liked. He offered on the Soloing forum to do a similar thing for the raps.<br><br>I haven't had the nerve to go back to TD yet after my 16hr marathon to get through 54 and still blinking at the idea that I'm 55.  I'll prob start grinding again this weekend. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td alig